{
    "title": "אַתָּה ה׳, מָגֵן בַּעֲדִי | Attah Adonai Magen Ba’adi, a piyyut by R’ Fradji Shawat (late 16th c.)",
    "author": "Jonah Rank",
    "coauthors": [
        {
            "name": "Jonah Rank",
            "bio": "Rabbi Jonah Rank is President and Rosh Yeshivah of <a href=\"https://hebrewseminary.org\">Hebrew Seminary</a>: A Rabbinical School for the Deaf and Hearing. An award-winning Jewish songwriter, Rabbi Rank earned an MA in Jewish Thought and was ordained in 2015 at the Jewish Theological Seminary of America. Rabbi Rank has been involved in Jewish education for many years and served as the Maskil (“Teacher-of-Tradition”) at the Shaar Shalom Synagogue in Halifax, Nova Scotia, where his spouse, Rabbi Dr. Raysh Weiss, served as Senior Rabbi. While living in Canada, Rabbi Rank initiated the annual Halifax Communal Beit Midrash, and collaborated with the community’s Education Committee in rebooting the Halifax Joint Hebrew School. Following his family’s return to the U.S, he became the Director of the Shul School at Kehilat HaNahar in New Hope, Pennsylvania. While managing the supplementary school, Rabbi Rank co-led a Virtual Youth Arts Beit Midrash serving youth across five states, designed a virtual reality Purim carnival, and created curricular materials for young Jews to engage with Jewish notions of responsibility towards marginalized communities and to the planet. Rabbi Rank has authored several academic articles, served as the Managing Editor of <em>Zeramim: An Online Journal of Applied Jewish Studies</em>, and is currently editing <em>Siddur Kanfey HaShekhinah</em>, a forthcoming traditional Ashkenazi Hebrew prayer book, where the language referring to God is with feminine grammar. An advocate for civic causes, Rabbi Rank was appointed in 2021 to the Environmental Advisory Council in the Township of Lower Makefield, Pennsylvania. Rabbi Rank’s recently moved with his family to Natick, Massachusetts.",
            "website": "http://jonahrank.com",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/jonah-rank-96x96.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/jonah-rank"
        },
        {
            "name": "Fradji Sawat",
            "bio": "The kabbalist Fradji Shawat (mid-16th c. till early 17th c.) was born in Fes (<span class=\"hebrew\">פאס</span>), Morocco, and later moved to Béja (<span class=\"hebrew\">באג׳ה</span>), Tunisia. Béja’s locals evidently did not at first care much for him but later grew fond of him. Jews who later wrote Tunisian Judeo-Arabic folk-songs about him yearly visited Shawat’s grave in Testour, Tunisia him. Rabbi Shawat’s songs were forgotten for nearly half a millennium.",
            "website": "",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Keith-Evans-Green-Tree-Yellow-Field-CC-BY-SA-250x250.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/fradji-sawat"
        }
    ],
    "date": "2019-04-22",
    "last_updated": "2021-03-15",
    "excerpt": "A (kosher-for-Passover) prayer for redemption from exile. . . .",
    "content": "[expander_maker id=\"1\" more=\"TABLE HELP\" less=\"close\"]\r\n<p />\r\n<u style=\"text-underline-offset: 5px;\">TOGGLE COLUMNS (on/off)</u>: <div id=\"column-toggle-container\"></div>\r\n<p />ADJUST COLUMN POSITIONS: select the column header cell and drag it where you want. <strong><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/images/column-drag6.gif\" rel=\"lightbox\">show me!</a></strong>\r\n<p />COPY INDIVIDUAL COLUMN(S): use <a href=\"https://merribithouse.net/copytables/\">CopyTables</a>, a browser extension.\r\n<hr />\r\n[/expander_maker]\r\n<p />\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nאַתָּה ה׳, מָגֵן בַּעֲדִי<br />\nתֹּאחַז יְמִינְךָ לְסַעֲדִי.<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nYou, Adonai—my Defender<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Psalms 3:4.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>—<br />\nhold with Your right hand<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Cf. Psalms 139:10.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> to support me.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nאֶשְׁאַל, אֱלֹהַי, מִמְּךָ דְרוֹר<br />\nלָצֵאת לְחׇפְשִׁי מֵעֳנִי וּבוֹר,<br />\nתָּשִׂים לְפָנַי מַחֲשָׁךְ לְאוֹר<br />\nוּבְדַרְכְּךָ, יָהּ, תָּכִין צַעֲדִי,<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nOf you—my God—I ask for the liberty<br />\nto go free from impoverishment and baseness.<br />\nReplace the darkness before me with light,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_3');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Cf. Isaiah 42:16.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_3', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;<br />\nand prep my step along Your way, Yah.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nנָא חִישׁ וְשַׁנֵּס עֹז קִנְאָתְךָ,<br />\nוּלְבַשׁ כְּשִׁרְיוֹן הוֹד צִדְקָתְךָ<br />\nכּֽוֹבַע יְשׁוּעָה שִׂים בְּרֹאשְׁךָ,<br />\nוּגְאַל עֲדָתִי מִיַּד שׁוֹדְדִי!<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nPlease—hasten, and bind the glory of Your zealousness,<br />\nand wear the glory of Your righteousness like a tune-ic.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_4');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Shawat’s Hebrew <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">כְּשִׁרְיוֹן</span> (keshiryon) does not match up with Isaiah’s original <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">כְּשִׁרְיָן</span> (keshiryan) in Isaiah 59:17. The exact meaning of each word is elusive, but Isaiah’s term usually refers to some sort of garb, but Shawat’s might be a bit more musical in sound, even if ultimately God is being asked to wear something.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_4', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;<br />\nPlace the hood of redemption<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_5');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Isaiah 59:17.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_5', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> upon Your head,<br />\nand redeem my congregation from the hand of the force that pillages me.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nיָהּ, תֵּן מְהֵרָה יָד בְּאוֹיְבִי,<br />\nהוֹצֵא הֲמוֹנַי מִכְּלוּא שְׁבִי!<br />\nיַעְלוּ לְאֶֽרֶץ נַחֲלַת צְבִי,<br />\nאָז יִרְבְּצוּ שָׁם נָמֵר עִם גְּדִי.<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nYah, quickly prop a hand by my enemy;<br />\nrelease my multitudes from the prison<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_6');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[6]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Jeremiah 37:4.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_6', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> of captivity!<br />\nLet them go up to the land of the inheritance of the buck-like<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_7');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[7]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Jeremiah 3:19.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_7', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>;<br />\nthen the leopard and the goat shall crouch there together.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_8');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[8]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Isaiah 11:6.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_8', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nפָּנִים בְּפָנִים יִרְאוּ הוֹדְךָ<br />\nחוֹפֵף עֲלֵיהֶם תּוֹךְ מְעוֹנְךָ,<br />\nתַּשְׁקֵם כְּמֵאָז נַֽחַל עֶדְנְךָ,<br />\nיִרְאֶה וְיֵבוֹשׁ צָר וּבוֹגְדִי.<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nLet them see Your glory face-to-face<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_9');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[9]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Deuteronomy 5:4.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_9', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>;<br />\nshield them<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_10');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[10]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Deuteronomy 33:12.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_10', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> amidst Your abode.<br />\nAs had been back then, let them drink from the stream of Your Edenism<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_11');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_11');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[11]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_11\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Another translation of <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">עֶדְנְךָ</span> (ednekha, “Your Eden[ism]”) could be “Your delight” or “Your joy.” Compare with Psalms 36:9.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_11', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>;<br />\nlet the enemy<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_12');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_12');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[12]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_12\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> According to one manuscript, “the enemy” should be “my enemy.”&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_12', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> and my deceiver behold and be ashamed.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nרָצוֹן כְּצִנָּה חִישׁ לְעַטְּרִי,<br />\nשָׁלוֹם יַעֲשֶׂה לִי גַם לְעוֹזְרִי,<br />\nיִפְרַח כְּבוֹדִי יַעֲשֶׂה פְרִי,<br />\nאָז יִהְיֶה צַר רָץ לְכַבְּדִי.<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nLet the Will<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_13');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_13');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[13]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_13\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> The word “Will” (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">רָצוֹן</span>, ratson) is a synonym in Kabbalah (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">קַבָּלָה</span>, Jewish mysticism) for God’s most ineffable and least tangible aspect: Keter (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">כֶּֽתֶר</span>, “Crown”).&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_13', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> be a shield to coronate me,<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_14');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_14');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[14]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_14\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Cf. Psalm 5:13.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_14', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;<br />\ngranting peace to me as well as to my helper.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_15');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_15');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[15]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_15\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> I Chronicles 12:19.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_15', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;<br />\nLet my substance blossom and bear fruit;<br />\nthen will the travail traverse to revere me.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nגִּילָה אֲעוֹרֵר יוֹם, לְבֵיתְךָ<br />\nתָּשִׁיב שְׁבוּת אֶת־עַם עֲדָתְךָ<br />\nלַחֲזוֹת בְּנֹֽעַם זִיו כְּבוֹדְךָ,<br />\nשָׁם יְהוֹדְךָ צוּר מְעוֹדְדִי,<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nI will arouse joy on the day<br />\nthat You return the nation of Your congregation to Your house—<br />\nSeeing the pleasantness<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_16');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_16');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[16]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_16\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Cf. Psalm 27:4.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_16', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> of the brow of Your glory.<br />\nThat nation will there thank You, rock who encourages me.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_17');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_17');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[17]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_17\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Cf. Psalms 147:6.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_17', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nיָחִיד, חֲרוֹנְךָ עַל אֱדֹם שְׁפֹךְ,<br />\nוַעְרָב כְּשַׁבְּלוּל תֶּֽמֶס יַהֲלֹךְ,<br />\nוּלְיוֹדְעֶֽיךָ—חַסְדְּךָ מְשֹׁךְ,<br />\nיֵלְכוּ גְאוּלִים לְבֵית מוֹעֲדִי!<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nSingular One, pour out Your wrath over Edom,<br />\nand emulsify, (un)like a snail melting and beyond.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_18');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_18');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_18\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[18]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_18\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Psalms 58:9.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_18').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_18', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nClasp onto Your lovingkindness for the sake of those who know You;<br />\nlet them go, redeemed, towards the house of my meeting.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"he\">\nחָזָק, עֲנֵנִי מִזְּבוּלְךָ<br />\nשִׁירִי תְּמוּר שַׁי קַח בְּחַסְדְּךָ<br />\nחַדֵּשׁ בְּקִרְבִּי רֽוּחַ קׇדְשְׁךָ<br />\nתִּשְׁכֹּן סְבִיבִי, צוּר מְלַמְּדִי!<br />\n</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"en\">\nStrong one! Answer me from Your heavens;<br />\nwith lovingkindness, take my song in exchange for a sacrificial gift.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_19');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_19');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_19\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[19]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_19\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Cf. Psalms 69:30–31.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_19').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_19', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\nAnew in my midst<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_20');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_20');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_20\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[20]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_20\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Psalms 51:12.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_20').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_20', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script> the spirit of Your holiness;<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_21');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_21');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_21\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[21]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_21\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Psalms 51:13.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_21').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_21', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script><br />\ndwell around me, my Rock who trains me.<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_22');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_22');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_22\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[22]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_22\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Psalms 144:1.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_22').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_22', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>Note the signature acrostic in this piyyut, &#8220;Ani Fradji Ḥazak.&#8221; The kabbalist Fradji Shawat (the author of this poem) was born in Fes (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">פאס</span>), Morocco, and later moved to Béja (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">באג׳ה</span>), Tunisia. Béja’s locals evidently did not at first care much for him but later grew fond of him (Hazan, p. 14). Leopold Zunz dated Shawat to the mid-16th century (<em>Literaturgeschichte der synagogalen Poeseie</em> [Berlin, 1865], p. 550). Shawat lived into the start of the 17th century. Jews who later wrote Tunisian Judeo-Arabic folk-songs about him yearly visited Shawat’s grave in Testour, Tunisia him. Rabbi Shawat’s songs were forgotten for nearly half a millennium (Hazan, p. 14). </p>\n<p>Translated and with commentary by Rabbi Jonah Rank in preparation for Passover 5779 (2019)—based on Ephraim Hazan, <em>The Poems of Fradji Shawat: Critical Edition with Introduction and Commentary</em> (Ben-Zvi Institute: Jerusalem, 1976) (Hebrew), pp. 78–79. | <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">תרגם ופירש הר׳ יונה גילון לבית אסתר איטע והר׳ רפאל פרץ בהכנתו לחג פסח בשנת ה׳תשע״ט—ומבוסס בספרושל  אפרים חזן (העורך), שירי פרג׳י שוואט (הוצאת מכון צבי של יד יצחק בן-צבי והאוניברסיטה העברית בירושלים: ירושלים, ה׳תשל״ו) (שירי גלות וגאולה ו׳) עמ׳ עח–עט.</span></p>\n<p>This work was first published on 17 April 2019 at Rabbi Jonah Rank&#8217;s blog, <a href=\"https://jonahrank.wordpress.com/2019/04/17/a-kosher-for-passover-prayer-for-redemption-from-exile/\">here</a>.</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<p>[gview file=&#8221;https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Attah-Adonai-Magen-Baadi-Jonah-Rank-trans.-2019.pdf&#8221;]</p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">[<a id=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1\">+</a>]</span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Psalms 3:4.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Cf. Psalms 139:10.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_3');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >3</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Cf. Isaiah 42:16.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_4');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >4</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Shawat’s Hebrew <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">כְּשִׁרְיוֹן</span> (keshiryon) does not match up with Isaiah’s original <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">כְּשִׁרְיָן</span> (keshiryan) in Isaiah 59:17. The exact meaning of each word is elusive, but Isaiah’s term usually refers to some sort of garb, but Shawat’s might be a bit more musical in sound, even if ultimately God is being asked to wear something.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_5');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >5</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Isaiah 59:17.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_6\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_6');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >6</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Jeremiah 37:4.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_7\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_7');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >7</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Jeremiah 3:19.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_8\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_8');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >8</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Isaiah 11:6.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_9\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_9');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >9</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Deuteronomy 5:4.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_10\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_10');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >10</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Deuteronomy 33:12.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_11\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_11');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >11</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Another translation of <span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">עֶדְנְךָ</span> (ednekha, “Your Eden[ism]”) could be “Your delight” or “Your joy.” Compare with Psalms 36:9.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_12\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_12');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >12</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">According to one manuscript, “the enemy” should be “my enemy.”</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_13\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_13');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >13</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">The word “Will” (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">רָצוֹן</span>, ratson) is a synonym in Kabbalah (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">קַבָּלָה</span>, Jewish mysticism) for God’s most ineffable and least tangible aspect: Keter (<span class=\"hebrew\" lang=\"he\">כֶּֽתֶר</span>, “Crown”).</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_14\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_14');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >14</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Cf. Psalm 5:13.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_15\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_15');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >15</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">I Chronicles 12:19.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_16\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_16');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >16</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Cf. Psalm 27:4.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_17\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_17');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >17</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Cf. Psalms 147:6.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_18\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_18');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >18</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Psalms 58:9.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_19\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_19');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >19</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Cf. Psalms 69:30–31.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_20\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_20');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >20</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Psalms 51:12.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_21\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_21');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >21</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Psalms 51:13.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_22\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_22');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >22</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Psalms 144:1.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('+'); } function footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1() { if (jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').is(':hidden')) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); } else { footnote_collapse_reference_container__1(); } } function footnote_moveToReference__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } } function footnote_moveToAnchor__1(p_str_TargetID) { footnote_expand_reference_container__1(); var l_obj_Target = jQuery('#' + p_str_TargetID); if (l_obj_Target.length) { jQuery( 'html, body' ).delay( 0 ); jQuery('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: l_obj_Target.offset().top - window.innerHeight * 0.2 }, 380); } }</script>",
